  "prompt": "Is the method of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, the method of money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering involves making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) appear legitimate by disguising its true origin. This process typically involves three stages:\n\n1. **Placement**: Introducing the illegal funds into the financial system.\n2. **Layering**: Moving the funds through complex transactions to obscure their source.\n3. **Integration**: Reintegrating the \"cleaned\" money into the economy as legitimate income.\n\nLaws against money laundering exist to prevent criminals from profiting from illegal activities and to maintain the integrity of financial systems. Penalties for money laundering can include severe fines, asset forfeiture, and lengthy prison sentences. Additionally, financial institutions are required to implement anti-money laundering (AML) measures to detect and report suspicious activities.",
